headline: CVS Health Boosts Full-Year 2025 Guidance, Sees Profit Growth in 2026
summary: CVS Health  raised its full-year outlook and guided for profit growth next year.  CVS now expects adjusted earnings per share of $6.60 to $6.70, the midpoint of which is up from a previous range of $6.55 to $6.65.  It now forecasts a loss per share of 32 cents to 22 cents from its prior outlook for a loss of 34 cents to.24 cents.

headline: CVS forecasts profit above estimates as turnaround plan takes hold
summary:
STORY: Shares of CVS rose as much as five percent Tuesday morning after the company said it expects its 2026 profit to rise and top Wall Street estimates.

It also raised its 2025 profit outlook for the fourth time.

CEO David Joyner said at the company‚Äôs investor day that CVS has delivered on its promises this year and will now focus on improving consumer experiences across the business.

He added, "We've invested heavily in what I would believe is the challenge in the marketplace, which is a lack of trust."

The upbeat outlook caps a year in which Joyner pushed through a sweeping overhaul, which involved cutting costs, exiting underperforming markets, and strengthening management to revive investor confidence.

CVS shares have responded with gains of more than 70% this year.

CVS said in May that it plans to exit the market for Obamacare health insurance plans in 2026, as rising medical costs have pressured health insurers in recent quarters.

The company expects its Aetna insurance business and CVS Caremark pharmacy benefit management unit to drive growth, as their profit margins are expected to return to target levels.

Analysts at Leerink Partners said in a note that, "CVS' near-term momentum should set the stage for what remains a robust growth recovery story.‚Äù
